loc: Kwatu Lodge, Ketu River (Elevala River tributary), Western Province
rmk: Singing well not far from the lodge. IOC 3.5 gives poecilurus as coastal NG, whereas I have found Little Bronze types well inland here and at Karawari on the Sepik. I cannot distinguish either song or alarm call from that of Gould's Bronze Cuckoo (russatus of some authorities) in Australia, and I have not seen anything that looks like Gould's here in PNG despite the recent Cuckoos monograph splitting them and giving it (Gould's) as widespread in NG
